                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 16.718,
                                "byte_start": 89004,
                                "byte_stop": 155877,
                                "text": "This case concerns 20 U.S.C. section 1097(a) which declares it a felony to misapply federally insured student loan funds, knowing and willfully."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.718,
                                "stop": 34.691,
                                "byte_start": 155877,
                                "byte_stop": 227871,
                                "text": "The question presented is whether Section 1097(a) demanded allegation and proof that the defendant specifically intented to defraud someone, either the United States as loan guarantor or another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.691,
                                "stop": 47.795,
                                "byte_start": 227871,
                                "byte_stop": 280220,
                                "text": "We hold that the government need not prove that the defendant had an intent to defraud the United States or another and affirm the judgment of the Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.795,
                                "stop": 62.245,
                                "byte_start": 280220,
                                "byte_stop": 338003,
                                "text": "The federally insured student loan program involved in this case works as follows: Banks lend money to students pursuing post secondary education."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.245,
                                "stop": 74.268,
                                "byte_start": 338003,
                                "byte_stop": 386173,
                                "text": "The lenders send checks covering tuition directly to the educational institution which credits the bank\u0027s loan against the student\u0027s tuition debt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.268,
                                "stop": 99.731,
                                "byte_start": 386173,
                                "byte_stop": 487946,
                                "text": "The government guarantees payment of the loan to the students default, if the student withdraws before the end of the term, the school must return to the bank the unused portion of the loan, if the school does not return the money, the student and if she default, the government will be obligated to repay the loan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.731,
                                "stop": 117.734,
                                "byte_start": 487946,
                                "byte_stop": 560044,
                                "text": "Defendant Bates was the chief financial officer of the school that received federally insured loans according to the indictment, Bates repeatedly diverted unused loan funds to the school\u0027s owners instead of making refunds to the bank."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.734,
                                "stop": 138.88,
                                "byte_start": 560044,
                                "byte_stop": 644576,
                                "text": "For this alleged conduct, he was charged with 12 violations of 1097(a), the indictment alleged that Bates knowingly and willfully misapplied student\u0027s loan funds but they it did not alleged in addition that he acted with an intent to injure or defraud the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.88,
                                "stop": 150.706,
                                "byte_start": 644576,
                                "byte_stop": 691910,
                                "text": "The District Court held that misapplication on the Section 1097(a) required such an allegation and therefore dismiss the indictment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 150.706,
                                "stop": 153.172,
                                "byte_start": 691910,
                                "byte_stop": 701732,
                                "text": "The Seventh Circuit reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.172,
                                "stop": 165.081,
                                "byte_start": 701732,
                                "byte_stop": 749380,
                                "text": "In conflict with the Eleventh Circuit, the Seventh Circuit held that intent to defraud is not an element of the crime defined in Section 1097(a)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.081,
                                "stop": 168.591,
                                "byte_start": 749380,
                                "byte_stop": 763381,
                                "text": "Our decision today dissolves that conflict."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.591,
                                "stop": 187.363,
                                "byte_start": 763381,
                                "byte_stop": 838509,
                                "text": "The word \u0022intent to defraud\u0022 to not appear in the text of Section 1097(a) but they do appear in the text of a neighboring provision 20 U.S.C. 1097(d) passed at the same time as Section 1097(a)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.363,
                                "stop": 202.275,
                                "byte_start": 838509,
                                "byte_stop": 898173,
                                "text": "This Court has said in similar context when Congress includes language in one section and omits it from a closely place section of the same statute courts should not add what Congress omitted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.275,
                                "stop": 230.705,
                                "byte_start": 898173,
                                "byte_stop": 1011858,
                                "text": "Bates emphasized is that another statute 18 U.S.C. Section 656 which prohibits the willful misapplication of bank funds, similarly does not now contain an intent to defraud requirement but that statute, as originally written, did contain such as requirement, the requirement was dropped out during the technical revision of the criminal code."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 230.705,
                                "stop": 248.372,
                                "byte_start": 1011858,
                                "byte_stop": 1082493,
                                "text": "Courts have continued to read and intent to defraud requirement into Section 656, concerned that without it even unauthorized loan, every an authorized loan by a bank officer might be turned into a federal offense."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 248.372,
                                "stop": 281.793,
                                "byte_start": 1082493,
                                "byte_stop": 1216240,
                                "text": "We assume, without deciding, that Section 656 is correctly read to retain an intent to defraud element but Section 1097(a) is differently situated, Section 1097(a) never contained an intent to defraud a requirement and there is no risk under the Seventh Circuit\u0027s contraction that near maladministration or unwise use of funds would fall within Section 1097(a)\u0027s compass."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 281.793,
                                "stop": 284.369,
                                "byte_start": 1216240,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The decision affirming the Seventh Circuit\u0027s judgment is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
